# .npmignore — generated by agenticaiplugin:npm-publish
#
# Privacy-safe defaults. Inverse logic of .gitignore: this excludes files
# from the published tarball. npm always auto-includes package.json, README,
# LICENSE, CHANGELOG, and the file referenced by `main`/`bin` regardless
# of this list — so you never need to whitelist them here.
#
# Prefer `package.json` `files[]` for explicit allowlisting on tightly-
# scoped libraries. This file is the broad-defaults approach: include
# everything except known-bad patterns.

# ─── Claude Code workspace ────────────────────────────────────────
# Reference: Check Point Research found .claude/settings.local.json
# in 428 of ~46,500 npm packages, with credentials in 30+ of them.
.claude/
.claude.local/
CLAUDE.md
claudedocs/

